\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did she die before your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. She died in St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 James\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 . She had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 A long time before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh yes. I should say me mother were about - dead about nine year - ten years before father died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Mother? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 Chapeltown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 . She was me mother's mother, me - me grandma were ninety when she died. She only had her and her brother, mother's brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Is Chapeltown near Leeds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 I think so, just outside of Leeds, it is in Leeds - it's just outside of Leeds I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Do you know if she had any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Mother was in service. Yes. That's when she got married to me dad when he was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 had she always been in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. Oh no, she worked on munitions, I'm sorry, when the war was on. She was in the canteen. She was there practically all the war.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 That was while you were a child then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 While I was going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did she work full time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. Well about - we'll say between five and half past, I know it was late when she got home. I was home from school when she came home y
ou see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Who looked after you while your mother was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Grandma. Mother's mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Can you remember how many rooms there were in the house in Armley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes, we'd - we'd two - we'd two attics, two bedrooms, a bathroom, a kitchen, a sitting room and a wash cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 It was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 quite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  a big house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. It was fourteen pound a year rates then. I was on me own then when dad died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did anybody else besides your parents and your brother and sister live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No. Oh yes, I had
 a lodger once but they didn't live there while I've been here, oh it's years since, I took a lodger in when the war was on we had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Which war was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Evacuees. This last one. Mother's mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Your grandma lived with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Lived with us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did your mother have anyone to help in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No. Only us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. Done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Me grandma used to sew for us but not mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did your grandma make things as well as mend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 She used to make - us little pinafores to go to school in. And - our little dresses she could do but that's all I know. I know }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 who}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  used to make us pinafores 'cos they were very nice. They had those frills on you know. I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 But your other clothes ere all bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 All bought, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Do you know where they were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 In Leeds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Any particular shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Well I don't know, mother never used to t
ell us. That's what the doctor said, why didn't mother tell me about this? I said, well I don't know, she says, she ought to have got into touch with - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Would the clothes that were bought for you were they always were new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 How frequently did you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
Oh we 've had 'em at Whitsuntide, we've had them at Easter. We've had them twice or three times a year - when mother could afford to buy them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Were there times when she was less well off and couldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
Well that's right, I mean to say, she didn't always get a lot off grandma you see grandma only got ten shillings a week when she - when she was pensioned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 When was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 When she was living with mother. And then she had a pension she use
d to draw every month in Leeds. I don't know what it was but I know I - we - I've gone with her for it. It was some kind of a pension she'd saved in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Was this before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 It was while we were living with her, yes. Well - while I - while I was w
orking then, not - when I was at school. She used to brought for in the museum in Leeds if you know where it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 What about shoes, did you have shoes fairly frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh yes. Yes. When we were needing them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did your father help your mother at all in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
Oh - oh - not in the house. Yes, is she were needed it he used to bake and cook dinner and - oh he could do anything in that line. But they didn't ask him, only when mother was ill and we was out working he'd do it. When he retired but he didn't -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 But before 1918, when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 When we - when we - no, he didn't do ought then, no. He could do but he didn't do because we used to do it, me sister and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 So at that time he didn't do anything in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 He didn't do any cleaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 What about the fire, die he make the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 he'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
 make the fire, yes. If it needed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 What about decorating or repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes, he once d
id the - he did - when we had a burst at Armley, he - did - gathered all the ice down and he repaired the roof. As far as he could but still we had to get a joiner in 'cos there was jobs he couldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did he do any improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh yes, he decorated, he decorated the kitchen, he did it beautiful - himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 When you were a small child did he do anything like dressing or undressing or bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Well I suppose he did love, but I couldn't say that you see, no, I don't think he did, mother'd do it. I don't - I never }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 heard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  her say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did he read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh no. Mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Would he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh - yes. He'd take me anywhere would me dad. Yes. I could go anywher
e with him - I do - I could now if he was here. That's where I feel it when mother died, we went all over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Would your father look after you when your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Certainly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 As a small child did you have any tasks to carry out at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
No, not really, no, I did as I was told if that's what you mean, and - I never - and me mother said I was a very good child, she said, she could put down with anything and I'd play for hours and there were a little girl next door to 'em in Arml
ey and I'd go in there and I could read me - me mother could go anywhere. She said, I was a very contented child and they took me to Nottingham once and - they were having a party and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 we
\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  traveled over - well I say, we hadn't traveled over night - we'd go
ne and me mother had a - used to suffer with these bilious attacks, well she had to go to bed. They put me to bed, me auntie, and - they said never heard a muff out of me, they were singing and dancing, never heard a muff out of me while next morning, tha
t was at Nottingham where me dad came from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 But as far as doing any jobs in the house was concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh - me, I can do anything, I can do -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 But when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes, I used to wash up for mother. Used to clean the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276634\charrsid13047356 shoes}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  and I used to dust for her, wash up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did you have particular jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No, not set out for us, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 What about the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Me sister. Oh yes, she'd do - occasionally but she put it onto me 'cos her were the eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 How long did you go on doing this, did you go on doing it after you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. Well, up 'til me sister got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 As an older child did you do anything to help your younger brother and sister?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Well me brother was older than me. Yes. I hel
ped me sister, yes, I helped undress her for mother if she wasn't well. Put her shoes on and wash her and bath her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did your younger sister do anything to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No. No, me moth
er used to put us if we weren't tired and - specially at weekend when we weren't going to school we'd go about eight or nine. But she didn't force us to go to bed and she never left us. Not on our own, not like they do now. Oh no. Oh she were frightened t
o death if she left us, she would think we were doing - you know - oh had a beautiful mother. And a father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 How old were you when you started putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh - nine or ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did you share the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 bedroom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  or the bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 I did, with 
me - no, we'd - we did when we were babies, 'cos mother hadn't a lot coming in and then she got us when we got older than me sister used to knock about a lot and then she got a bed of her own, we had a bed of our won while me sister got married. We'd a be
d each, she bought us a wooden one each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 And you shared the bed, that one bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 The bed. In one bedroom, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 What were the sleeping arrangements for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Well - mother - grandma had a - grandma slept in the - mother and father h
ad a bed of their own - a bedroom of their own and grandma slept in the small one, on her own. But I were a terror, I'd love to sleep with her but - you know, I never did do, sleep with her. When she were ill I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 When you and your sister were sharing a bedroom was that one of the attics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No, it was an ordinary bedroom. Not on attic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 I thought you had two bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 We had two bedrooms at Armley but she wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 living}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  then love. Grandma died before mother. Yes, of her own and mother had a bedroom of her own. And we had a bedroom of us own. We'd three bedrooms then before we took the other one where the attics were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 This first house at Armley you had three bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. Yes. And an attic. Me brother slept in the attic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 And the downstairs rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 As I've told you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did you have a bathroom there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 As a small child how often were you bathed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh every week. Tice a week sometimes. Mother used to say, come on, I'll give you a bath and - of cour
se we could bath ourselves. And I've - many }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
 I've been at home, before - when - when I've been at home I'd rather get in the bath than have a wash. You know, a wash. Oh I love to get in a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 As a small child when did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Every week. Tice a week if we wanted them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Where did you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 In the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 kitchen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 . Have company we used to have it in the sitting room. The living - you know - this - mother put a fire in and we'd have it in there. Many a time we've had us meals when we haven't had company in the sitting room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Where did your mother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 In the kitchen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 What cooking arrangements were there?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 A gas oven. And a fire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 And oven with the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No, yes. But dad got a gas oven from the Corporation that was one someone had brought in, a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 secondhand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  one and at Armley where we've left - where I we've left, where I went before I came here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 The first house you were in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh, she cooked in the kit
chen love. The first house, and then we had a sitting room but then we used to go in there when - to sit in you know like you might - we didn't live in the kitchen. We just did the meals - had the meals in and cook in and then we went in the sitting room.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Had she got a gas cooker then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 No. Just the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276634\charrsid13047356 ordinary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  oven. Yes, a fire oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 When you were a small child going to school about what time would you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh - round about eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Who would be present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
Mother. Me sister and I. And me brother. And dad. He had to be on the Corporation at nine, he had to - well, he had to be down there about half past eight to - to report in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 So you all had breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 What sort of a meal was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh could have bacon or - or anything there were, mother always had bacon in but of course there weren't these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 cornflakes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  going a lot then. And we had porridge if we wanted it. Or - Quaker Oats. Anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did you have something to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh yes, tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did you have anything special for a Sunday breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
Yes, we've had - mother's got - sausage or liver with it with - we've got bacon and liver and - and eggs with it, and then she used to fry - the toast like they were in fat, what was left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 What about your dinner?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh we always had a joint. At Sunday. And during the week. And chops and mother used to make meat potato pies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did you all go home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 About what time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
Be about one o'clock. Well we left school at twelve - we'd to be back for half past - when that was - as - if you're speaking as a child. Yes. We left school at twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did you have a pudding of some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 sort}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh yes, a milk pudding or
 a sponge pudding. Either a ginger pudding or an apple sponge or anything like that. Or a rice pudding or a sago pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 What about your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh we'd always a nice tea. With either salmon or - or specially on a Sunday. For tea we'd either have 
boiled ham or tongue or anything we wished. Anything like that. But on a Sunday we always used to have a bit of a - you know - mother used to open a tin of salmon and make a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 salad}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 then}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
 we'd have a tin of fruit if we didn't want ought like that. Oh yes, she fed us well did mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did you have fruit or anything during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. If we wanted it. Yes, she'd open a tin of fruit or a tine of crab or a tin salmon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did you have cake as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. Me mother used to bake her own cakes, she wouldn't have much bought. She used to bake }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 every}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356  Thursday. Make apple juice pies and cakes and tarts and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 And you'd have tea to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 What about going to bed, did you have something then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Yes. We had our - a bit of cake or a glass of milk or we could have had - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10122990\charrsid13047356 sandwich}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 
 of anything there were. If we'd had boiled ham for tea if there was any left mother'd make us a sandwich to go to bed on and either milk or a cup of tea. Could have anything like that. Or Horlicks or anything like that - Ovaltine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did your mother bake bread as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7497575 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Oh yes. And - and teacakes as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16253520 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15616576\charrsid13047356 Did she make jam or bottle fruit?
